==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hemoglobin
<hw>Hem"o*glo"bin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hemo-</ets> + <ets>globe</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>The normal coloring matter of the red blood corpuscles of
vertebrate animals. It is composed of hematin and globulin, and is also
called <altname>haematoglobulin</altname>. In arterial blood, it is
always combined with oxygen, and is then called
<stype>oxyhemoglobin</stype>. It crystallizes under different forms from
different animals, and when crystallized, is called
<stype>haematocrystallin</stype>. See <cref>Blood crystal</cref>, under
<er>Blood</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hemoglobinometer</ent>⟦br⟧
